<!DOCTYPE collection SYSTEM "BioC.dtd">
<collection><source>GO_Annotation</source><date>20130316</date><key>go_annotation.key</key><document><id>22912598</id><passage><infon key="type">abstract</infon><offset>107</offset><annotation id="22912598_1"><infon key="gene">CRC(47767)</infon><infon key="go-term">ecdysis-triggering hormone receptor activity|GO:0042654</infon><infon key="goevidence">NONE</infon><infon key="type">GOA</infon><location offset="740" length="138"/><text>Here we show that Cryptocephal (CRC), the Drosophila homolog of ATF4, is an ecdysone receptor coactivator that is specific for isoform B2.</text></annotation></passage><passage><infon key="type">abstract</infon><offset>1310</offset><annotation id="22912598_2"><infon key="gene">CRC(47767)</infon><infon key="go-term">ecdysis-triggering hormone receptor activity|GO:0042654</infon><infon key="goevidence">NONE</infon><infon key="type">GOA</infon><location offset="1798" length="169"/><text>Here, we show that the fruit fly Cryptocephal (CRC) protein is a specific coactivator for one of three isoforms of the receptor for the insect molting steroid, ecdysone.</text></annotation></passage><passage><infon key="type">paragraph</infon><offset>3264</offset><annotation id="22912598_3"><infon key="gene">CRC(47767)</infon><infon key="go-term">ecdysis-triggering hormone receptor activity|GO:0042654</infon><infon key="goevidence">NONE</infon><infon key="type">GOA</infon><location offset="3789" length="193"/><text>Here, we show that the bZIP transcription factor, CRC (FBgn0000370), binds the AF1 of isoform B2 to promote steroid-dependent expression of the peptide molting hormone, ETH (FBgn0028738; [14]).</text></annotation></passage><passage><infon key="type">paragraph</infon><offset>4044</offset><annotation id="22912598_4"><infon key="gene">CRC(47767)</infon><infon key="go-term">protein binding|GO:0005515</infon><infon key="goevidence">IPI</infon><infon key="type">GOA</infon><location offset="4296" length="117"/><text>Interaction (as judged by reporter activation) required the presence of both CRC-A and the AF1 of EcR-B2 (Figure 1A).</text></annotation><annotation id="22912598_5"><infon key="gene">CRC(47767)</infon><infon key="go-term">protein binding|GO:0005515</infon><infon key="goevidence">IPI</infon><infon key="type">GOA</infon><location offset="4556" length="289"/><text>The interaction surface provided by CRC was contained within the C-terminal three-quarters of the protein, a region that includes its bZIP and PEST domains, and C-terminal truncation of the protein to remove just the leucine zipper domain abolished the interaction with EcR-B2 (Figure 1B).</text></annotation></passage><passage><infon key="type">paragraph</infon><offset>5653</offset><annotation id="22912598_6"><infon key="gene">CRC(47767)</infon><infon key="go-term">protein binding|GO:0005515</infon><infon key="goevidence">IPI</infon><infon key="type">GOA</infon><location offset="5653" length="89"/><text>Binding of CRC to the amino-terminal region of EcR-B2 was confirmed in vitro (Figure 2A).</text></annotation></passage><passage><infon key="type">title_2</infon><offset>12788</offset><annotation id="22912598_7"><infon key="gene">CRC(47767)</infon><infon key="go-term">regulation of gene expression|GO:0010468</infon><infon key="goevidence">IDA</infon><infon key="type">GOA</infon><location offset="12788" length="32"/><text>CRC Regulation of ETH Expression</text></annotation></passage><passage><infon key="type">paragraph</infon><offset>13151</offset><annotation id="22912598_8"><infon key="gene">CRC(47767)</infon><infon key="go-term">regulation of gene expression|GO:0010468</infon><infon key="goevidence">IDA</infon><infon key="type">GOA</infon><location offset="13596" length="212"/><text>Compared to the control larvae, larvae with crc RNAi showed a 15-fold or greater reduction in ETH transcript levels (Figure 3A). Thus, CRC was cell-autonomously required in the Inka cells for full ETH expression.</text></annotation><annotation id="22912598_9"><infon key="gene">crc(47767)</infon><infon key="go-term">regulation of gene expression|GO:0010468</infon><infon key="goevidence">IDA</infon><infon key="type">GOA</infon><location offset="13596" length="212"/><text>Compared to the control larvae, larvae with crc RNAi showed a 15-fold or greater reduction in ETH transcript levels (Figure 3A). Thus, CRC was cell-autonomously required in the Inka cells for full ETH expression.</text></annotation></passage><passage><infon key="type">title_2</infon><offset>17260</offset><annotation id="22912598_10"><infon key="gene">CRC(47767)</infon><infon key="go-term">protein binding|GO:0005515</infon><infon key="goevidence">NONE</infon><infon key="type">GOA</infon><location offset="17260" length="57"/><text>CRC and EcR-B2 Interacted to Boost ETH Expression In Vivo</text></annotation><annotation id="22912598_11"><infon key="gene">EcR(35540)</infon><infon key="go-term">protein binding|GO:0005515</infon><infon key="goevidence">NONE</infon><infon key="type">GOA</infon><location offset="17260" length="57"/><text>CRC and EcR-B2 Interacted to Boost ETH Expression In Vivo</text></annotation></passage></document></collection>
